                                        "title":  "Doppelter Infinitiv · Double Infinitive",
                                        "text":  "When modal verbs (können, müssen, wollen, sollen, dürfen) are used in Perfekt, they do NOT use Partizip II. Instead, the infinitive of the modal verb is used, creating a double infinitive construction at the end of the sentence.",
                                        "bullets":  [
                                                        "Normal Perfekt: Ich habe das gemacht. (Partizip II)",
                                                        "Modal Perfekt: Ich habe das machen müssen. (double infinitive!)",
                                                        "The modal verb stays in infinitive form, NOT gemusst/gekonnt",
                                                        "This also applies to lassen, sehen, hören in Perfekt"
                                                    ]
                                    },
                                    {
